In 4.4 version without Lazy Loading, it loaded all components at the very first time and it took 30 Seconds to render landing page.
In 8.2 version with Lazy Loading, it loaded only required components for the landing page and it took around 500 MilliSeconds

And differential loading lets us serve up different bundles to different browsers and make our application even faster!  
It saves on average 7-20% in bundle size for Angular applications in modern browsers.

